name: Brewlab
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place is awesome. There’s two rooms, one with a coffee bar and one a makerspace with a bike fixing shop (!!!). Great spot to work. 

Taste: 4 / 5. The coffee was super well made, slightly on the acidic side but generally very balanced. Smooth taste.
visit_again: 5 - Would drive many hours to get to this place
vibe_thoughts: This place is awesome. There’s two rooms, one with a coffee bar and one a makerspace with a bike fixing shop (!!!). Great spot to work.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was super well made, slightly on the acidic side but generally very balanced. Smooth taste.

name: Well Coffeehouse
thoughts: Vibe: 5/5. Honestly didn’t expect such a cool vibe from a coffee shop off the highway but here we are. Good vibes great merch. Taste: 5/5. The coffee is incredible. So much so I bought merch.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
location:
7618 Hwy 70S
Unit 107
Nashville, TN 37221
United States
vibe_thoughts: Honestly didn’t expect such a cool vibe from a coffee shop off the highway but here we are. Good vibes great merch.
taste_thoughts: The coffee is incredible. So much so I bought merch.

name: Pink Hermit Cafe
thoughts: Vibe: 5/5. Super pink super cute. It’s located on the outside of a hotel but the hotel vibe doesn’t come through. Everyone super friendly as well. Taste: 4/5. Really good coffee as well!!
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
location:
231 Sixth Ave N
Nashville, TN  37219
United States
vibe_thoughts: Super pink super cute. It’s located on the outside of a hotel but the hotel vibe doesn’t come through. Everyone super friendly as well.
taste_thoughts: Really good coffee as well!!

name: Firehouse Coffee and Tea
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This is a cozy spot by the Sausalito docks. Has a bunch of working spots, great seating and lots of couches! More coffee places need couches imo. 

Taste: 4 / 5. The coffee was really good too. The espresso was balanced but the flavor came through.
visit_again: 5 - Would drive many hours to get to this place
vibe_thoughts: This is a cozy spot by the Sausalito docks. Has a bunch of working spots, great seating and lots of couches! More coffee places need couches imo.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was really good too. The espresso was balanced but the flavor came through.

name: Dr.ink
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Minimalistic, great music, great decor. Good wifi, amazing people. Very good scent. 

Taste: 4 / 5. I got a light sweet matcha which was really good! It was quite foamy, which I personally don’t mind. It tasted great.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
location: 77 N Almaden Ave Suite 70, San Jose, CA 95110
vibe_thoughts: Minimalistic, great music, great decor. Good wifi, amazing people. Very good scent.
taste_thoughts: I got a light sweet matcha which was really good! It was quite foamy, which I personally don’t mind. It tasted great.

name: Voyager Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place reminds me of college. There’s a bunch of people here studying, working, drawing, yapping, and it makes me super nostalgic. A lot of seating, huge windows, great place to spend hours on end. 

Taste: 5 / 5. Their menu has traditional coffee drinks, but has location inspired coffee drinks on top. I got the Manila, which was a Ube + Mango + Coconut drink, which I expected to be very sweet but was incredibly balanced and tasted great.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
location: 87 N San Pedro St, San Jose, CA 95110
vibe_thoughts: This place reminds me of college. There’s a bunch of people here studying, working, drawing, yapping, and it makes me super nostalgic. A lot of seating, huge windows, great place to spend hours on end.
taste_thoughts: Their menu has traditional coffee drinks, but has location inspired coffee drinks on top. I got the Manila, which was a Ube + Mango + Coconut drink, which I expected to be very sweet but was incredibly balanced and tasted great.

name: Red Rock Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Whatever you’re looking to do, this place is super cool. If you’re there to work, they have an upper area to do just that or if you’re there to hang out they have a bunch of seating. The place is well lit and the staff is very chill.

Taste: 3 / 5. The coffee was okay. The espresso taste was there, but it was a little too milky.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Whatever you’re looking to do, this place is super cool. If you’re there to work, they have an upper area to do just that or if you’re there to hang out they have a bunch of seating. The place is well lit and the staff is very chill.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was okay. The espresso taste was there, but it was a little too milky.

name: The Quarters Coffee House
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place is the perfect working environment. It’s unfortunate that they close early, because if not I’d work here for hours and hours. It’s a residential house (very nice house, might I add) where the bottom floor has been converted into a cafe. Great decor, good vibes, good music. 

Taste: 5 / 5. The coffee was also great, it was a hot day and the iced latte is what I needed. Was not watered down in the slightest.
visit_again: 5 - Would drive many hours to get to this place
vibe_thoughts: This place is the perfect working environment. It’s unfortunate that they close early, because if not I’d work here for hours and hours. It’s a residential house (very nice house, might I add) where the bottom floor has been converted into a cafe. Great decor, good vibes, good music.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was also great, it was a hot day and the iced latte is what I needed. Was not watered down in the slightest.

name: Black Oak Coffee Roasters
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place was super spacious, well lit, had a super cool backyard and lots of spaces to work. The vibes were high!

Taste: 4 / 5. The coffee was roasted inhouse and tasted great (bold espresso taste + not too milky). ALSO the banana bread was super tasty.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: This place was super spacious, well lit, had a super cool backyard and lots of spaces to work. The vibes were high!
taste_thoughts: The coffee was roasted inhouse and tasted great (bold espresso taste + not too milky). ALSO the banana bread was super tasty.

name: The lighthouse
thoughts: Vibe: 5/5. This is hidden away between huge corporate buildings but after stepping in you can’t tell you’re in the heart of capitalism. Very cozy and the people are super friendly! Taste: 4/5. I got the raspberry latte which was tasty but the raspberry syrup was a bit overpowering. The coffee taste was pretty enjoyable though.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
location:
685 Gateway Blvd
South San Francisco, CA 94080
United States
vibe_thoughts: This is hidden away between huge corporate buildings but after stepping in you can’t tell you’re in the heart of capitalism. Very cozy and the people are super friendly!
taste_thoughts: I got the raspberry latte which was tasty but the raspberry syrup was a bit overpowering. The coffee taste was pretty enjoyable though.

name: Mademoiselle Colette
thoughts: Vibe: 4 / 5. Super french. Super cafe. Not a work spot, but super chill to come hang out with people. Has outdoor seating. Taste: 4 / 5. Strong espresso taste. Well made. Cheaper than others I’ve had around.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
location: 816 Santa Cruz Ave, Menlo Park, CA 94025
vibe_thoughts: Super french. Super cafe. Not a work spot, but super chill to come hang out with people. Has outdoor seating.
taste_thoughts: Strong espresso taste. Well made. Cheaper than others I’ve had around.

name: Saint Frank’s Coffee
thoughts: Vibe: 2 / 5: It’s a shack with outdoor seating
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: It’s a shack with outdoor seating

name: Andytown Coffee Roasters
thoughts: Vibe: 5 / 5. Perfect decor! Super cute, lots of outdoor seating, much less indoors though. Cute music, cute setup. Really nice. Taste: 3 / 5. It’s bold. The espresso tastes very strong, which is good. It was a little too milky but generally super well made.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
location: 1302 El Camino Real, Menlo Park, CA 94025
vibe_thoughts: Perfect decor! Super cute, lots of outdoor seating, much less indoors though. Cute music, cute setup. Really nice.
taste_thoughts: It’s bold. The espresso tastes very strong, which is good. It was a little too milky but generally super well made.

name: Coffeebar
thoughts: Vibe: 5 / 5. Super cool work space! Big windows, good lighting, super spacious. Taste: 3 / 5. Very … basic. Not really a rich taste or make, which is not my vibe. Seems like I could make it.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: Super cool work space! Big windows, good lighting, super spacious.
taste_thoughts: Very … basic. Not really a rich taste or make, which is not my vibe. Seems like I could make it.

name: Canteen Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Super chill, great spot to work. LOVE the decor and everything. Good music, good people.

Taste: 5 / 5. Yes. Love this coffee. Strong espresso taste but not overpowering - didn’t really have notes of anything but super smooth and well made. Love.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Super chill, great spot to work. LOVE the decor and everything. Good music, good people.
taste_thoughts: Yes. Love this coffee. Strong espresso taste but not overpowering - didn’t really have notes of anything but super smooth and well made. Love.

name: Cafe Borrone
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Twas poppin! Good natural light, lots of people. Maybe a little too many, might’ve been a little congested but overall quite nice. 

Taste: 4 / 5. Really good coffee, loved the espresso flavor.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Twas poppin! Good natural light, lots of people. Maybe a little too many, might’ve been a little congested but overall quite nice.
taste_thoughts: Really good coffee, loved the espresso flavor.

name: Verve Coffee Roasters
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5
Love their backyard (except when it’s raining) and there is good indoor space which makes it perfect to work in. Good decor generally and feels like a very cozy place

Taste: 4 / 5
I usually get a cappuccino or latte here, which I enjoy. I just wish the coffee taste was stronger. Consistency and texture wise very nicely balanced.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Love their backyard (except when it’s raining) and there is good indoor space which makes it perfect to work in. Good decor generally and feels like a very cozy place
taste_thoughts: I usually get a cappuccino or latte here, which I enjoy. I just wish the coffee taste was stronger. Consistency and texture wise very nicely balanced.

name: Cafe Vittoria
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Pretty vintage, but a little crowded. It was hard to get by tables. If you’re looking for a good hangout, this is a great spot! Not a place you’d be able to work though. 

Taste: 3 / 5. Very standard coffee, little on the milky side and couldn’t taste the espresso much at all.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: Pretty vintage, but a little crowded. It was hard to get by tables. If you’re looking for a good hangout, this is a great spot! Not a place you’d be able to work though.
taste_thoughts: Very standard coffee, little on the milky side and couldn’t taste the espresso much at all.

name: 1369 Coffee
thoughts: Vibe: 5 / 5. Super cozy, super cute place. It’s raining and grey outside, and this is exactly where I’d wanna be in this weather. Not the most spacious, but it’s great. Taste: 5 / 5! Not sure what beans these are, but strong espresso taste and a super well made coffee. Coffee taste might be up there w sightglass.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
location:
757 Massachusetts Ave
Cambridge, MA 02139
United States
vibe_thoughts: Super cozy, super cute place. It’s raining and grey outside, and this is exactly where I’d wanna be in this weather. Not the most spacious, but it’s great.
taste_thoughts: ! Not sure what beans these are, but strong espresso taste and a super well made coffee. Coffee taste might be up there w sightglass.

name: Snowbird Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. Cute spot, very little seating but their merch was quite cute. Had great lighting. 

Taste: 3 / 5. Balanced and tasted smooth, the vanilla syrup wasn’t overpowering. Solid iced shaken espresso drink, nothing standout.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Cute spot, very little seating but their merch was quite cute. Had great lighting.
taste_thoughts: Balanced and tasted smooth, the vanilla syrup wasn’t overpowering. Solid iced shaken espresso drink, nothing standout.

name: Better Half Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Extremely cozy, gives old bar on a stormy winter night. Could spend hours working here. 

Taste: 4 / 5. Less bold of an espresso taste than I’d like, but quite balanced. Not super acidic or anything of the sort.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Extremely cozy, gives old bar on a stormy winter night. Could spend hours working here.
taste_thoughts: Less bold of an espresso taste than I’d like, but quite balanced. Not super acidic or anything of the sort.

name: Moka Coffee
thoughts: Vibe: 5 / 5. Quaint small cute. I liked the interior design a lot. Seating felt abundant even though it wasn’t a huge shop. Taste: 4 / 5. The espresso was bold and chocolatey. The milk wasn’t the smoothest, but very well could be a one off. They gave me my coffee in a takeout cup even though I was sat there ):
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Quaint small cute. I liked the interior design a lot. Seating felt abundant even though it wasn’t a huge shop.
taste_thoughts: The espresso was bold and chocolatey. The milk wasn’t the smoothest, but very well could be a one off. They gave me my coffee in a takeout cup even though I was sat there ):

name: Fayes
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Place has been around for a HOT minute. Not a lot of seating, but they have a really cool movie / DVD collection in the back. 

Taste: 3 / 5. Taste was okay. Got an iced coffee, tasted like milk.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Place has been around for a HOT minute. Not a lot of seating, but they have a really cool movie / DVD collection in the back.
taste_thoughts: Taste was okay. Got an iced coffee, tasted like milk.

name: Souvenir Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Hole in the wall style but they somehow fit a roastery and a decent amount of seating in here. Music on point, all the baristas were vibing.

Taste: 4 / 5. Little too foamy, but tasted really great! I like the espresso taste, which is def a big plus for their roasting.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Hole in the wall style but they somehow fit a roastery and a decent amount of seating in here. Music on point, all the baristas were vibing.
taste_thoughts: Little too foamy, but tasted really great! I like the espresso taste, which is def a big plus for their roasting.

name: CoffeeShop Micro Roastery
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Lots of natural light but a little cramped seating wise. Great outdoor seating though – place felt like it served a ton of regulars. It constantly smells like roasted beans, which was incredibly fun for me, but may not be for everyone.

Taste: 4 / 5. Good coffee – interestingly made my iced coffee with hot foamed milk which added an interesting texture to it that I enjoyed.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Lots of natural light but a little cramped seating wise. Great outdoor seating though – place felt like it served a ton of regulars. It constantly smells like roasted beans, which was incredibly fun for me, but may not be for everyone.
taste_thoughts: Good coffee – interestingly made my iced coffee with hot foamed milk which added an interesting texture to it that I enjoyed.

name: Abanico Coffee Roasters
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. Lots of natural light, which we love. Not a ton of seating which was surprising, but enough for people to get some stuff done.

Taste: 5 / 5. GREAT coffee. Very smooth, tasted very balanced. Pleasant aftertaste, overall great coffee.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Lots of natural light, which we love. Not a ton of seating which was surprising, but enough for people to get some stuff done.
taste_thoughts: GREAT coffee. Very smooth, tasted very balanced. Pleasant aftertaste, overall great coffee.

name: Linea Caffe
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. I visited this place a few hours after landing in SF from NYC. I was still freshly missing cornerstores, and this place gave me a wonderful fix. I also really like their font. 

Taste: 4 / 5. I’d wanted to try them for a while. They have a big roastery in another part of the city. Didn’t disappoint! Good coffee, was balanced. Little on the sweeter side and good aftertaste.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: I visited this place a few hours after landing in SF from NYC. I was still freshly missing cornerstores, and this place gave me a wonderful fix. I also really like their font.
taste_thoughts: I’d wanted to try them for a while. They have a big roastery in another part of the city. Didn’t disappoint! Good coffee, was balanced. Little on the sweeter side and good aftertaste.

name: Pinhole Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Could sit here for hours. I love the decor, very artsy, very photography centric. Great wall art and they have really cute pinhole merch. I especially love the wall behind the counter which has pinhole branded art. Love it. 

Taste: 5 / 5. The latte was so good. It was rich and creamy but tasted wonderful. The latte art was quite impressive too.
visit_again: 5 - Would drive many hours to get to this place
vibe_thoughts: Could sit here for hours. I love the decor, very artsy, very photography centric. Great wall art and they have really cute pinhole merch. I especially love the wall behind the counter which has pinhole branded art. Love it.
taste_thoughts: The latte was so good. It was rich and creamy but tasted wonderful. The latte art was quite impressive too.

name: Haus Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. This place is very homey. Good backyard seating, lots of place to sit and work. There’s also a haus cat. 

Taste: 4 / 5. The cortado was really good!! A little acidic but very smooth, with the bold espresso flavor I really like.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: This place is very homey. Good backyard seating, lots of place to sit and work. There’s also a haus cat.
taste_thoughts: The cortado was really good!! A little acidic but very smooth, with the bold espresso flavor I really like.

name: CoffeeShop
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Very hole in the wall place but really nice modern decor. They also had cool swag. They have no seating but have free wifi, which is a nice add. 

Taste: 4 / 5. The coffee was solid! Not very intense and pleasant espresso flavor. They also had a few baked goodies which tasted nice.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Very hole in the wall place but really nice modern decor. They also had cool swag. They have no seating but have free wifi, which is a nice add.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was solid! Not very intense and pleasant espresso flavor. They also had a few baked goodies which tasted nice.

name: Martha and Bros Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. Fun fact: this was the first cafe I visited after moving to SF. This is a very cozy spot. They don’t have wifi, but that doesn’t stop them from making it a great place to work / read. 
Taste: 3 / 5. I honestly thought the coffee was way too diluted. Still I give them the benefit of the doubt that it was a one-off.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: Fun fact: this was the first cafe I visited after moving to SF. This is a very cozy spot. They don’t have wifi, but that doesn’t stop them from making it a great place to work / read.
taste_thoughts: I honestly thought the coffee was way too diluted. Still I give them the benefit of the doubt that it was a one-off.

name: Red Bay Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Minimalistic, clean, very conducive to productivity. Huge island barista counter in the middle and plenty of seating. Big fan.

Taste: 4 / 5. I got the Saigon latte which was great! It had a mellow taste which I really enjoyed. The coffee wasn’t overwhelming and hit the right spots.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Minimalistic, clean, very conducive to productivity. Huge island barista counter in the middle and plenty of seating. Big fan.
taste_thoughts: I got the Saigon latte which was great! It had a mellow taste which I really enjoyed. The coffee wasn’t overwhelming and hit the right spots.

name: Java Beach at the zoo
thoughts:
Vibe: 4 / 5. This felt like a classic beach town coffee shop. Breezy, very well lit. Couldn’t sit here to work but I don’t think that’s the intended effect. 

Taste: 3 / 5. The coffee was okay. I got a cappuccino which was closer to a latte, which is fine, but I suppose the takeaway is that expect your drinks to feel a little diluted.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: This felt like a classic beach town coffee shop. Breezy, very well lit. Couldn’t sit here to work but I don’t think that’s the intended effect.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was okay. I got a cappuccino which was closer to a latte, which is fine, but I suppose the takeaway is that expect your drinks to feel a little diluted.

name: The Beanery
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. Great lighting, but this place was uninspiring. Felt like a beat down spot where no one, including the people running the place, wanted to be. 

Taste: 2 / 5. The coffee was really watered down so it almost felt like I was drinking a glass of cold milk.
visit_again: 1 - Would not visit again
vibe_thoughts: Great lighting, but this place was uninspiring. Felt like a beat down spot where no one, including the people running the place, wanted to be.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was really watered down so it almost felt like I was drinking a glass of cold milk.

name: Diamond Coffee and Pastry
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place is very cute, though I might be biased because I came here on a date. But I really like their decor, they have great spots to sit. This would make a great place to work. They have great desserts too. 

Taste: 4 / 5. The coffee was good! It was a strong espresso taste and blistering hot, which I really like.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: This place is very cute, though I might be biased because I came here on a date. But I really like their decor, they have great spots to sit. This would make a great place to work. They have great desserts too.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was good! It was a strong espresso taste and blistering hot, which I really like.

name: Earth Tone Cafe
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. This place is how I’d like to set up my eventual cafe. It has only a few spots to sit, but each one of them is very very cozy. They always have great music and great vibes. 

Taste: 5 / 5. Their banana latte might be one of my favorite coffee drinks. They used mashed bananas so the drink itself is chunky, which I really like. I haven’t seen this being done in many other coffee places, though I’m sure they’re not the first.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: This place is how I’d like to set up my eventual cafe. It has only a few spots to sit, but each one of them is very very cozy. They always have great music and great vibes.
taste_thoughts: Their banana latte might be one of my favorite coffee drinks. They used mashed bananas so the drink itself is chunky, which I really like. I haven’t seen this being done in many other coffee places, though I’m sure they’re not the first.

name: Union Coffee Roastery
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. This is an okay place to work, but a little hard to find outlets. They didn’t have wifi either. They do have good seating though. 

Taste: 3 / 5. The coffee here was okay. Too diluted so didn’t taste the best.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
vibe_thoughts: This is an okay place to work, but a little hard to find outlets. They didn’t have wifi either. They do have good seating though.
taste_thoughts: The coffee here was okay. Too diluted so didn’t taste the best.

name: California Kahve - Presidio
thoughts:
Vibe: 3 / 5. The surrounding area is great, but the truck itself is in a heavily trafficked spot where everyone’s coming to grab lunch. The walk afterwards is pristine though. 

Taste: 3 / 5. I got their seasonal special but received a matcha instead. The matcha was okay, but was too milky and the matcha taste (or any other flavor, which were added) didn’t come through at all.
visit_again: 2 - Would stop by if I stumble upon this place again
location: Presidio Tunnel Top, 210 Lincoln Blvd, San Francisco, CA 94123
vibe_thoughts: The surrounding area is great, but the truck itself is in a heavily trafficked spot where everyone’s coming to grab lunch. The walk afterwards is pristine though.
taste_thoughts: I got their seasonal special but received a matcha instead. The matcha was okay, but was too milky and the matcha taste (or any other flavor, which were added) didn’t come through at all.

name: The Buoy
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Super boujee, super fancy but also super cozy. A very unsuspecting spot, hard to tell what it is but once you’re inside it’s a great place to work and hang out. 

Taste: 4 / 5. I got a toasted coconut latte. The coconut flavor was good but REALLY strong. The first few sips were great, but once the flavor settled a little bit the last few were hard to get through.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: Super boujee, super fancy but also super cozy. A very unsuspecting spot, hard to tell what it is but once you’re inside it’s a great place to work and hang out.
taste_thoughts: I got a toasted coconut latte. The coconut flavor was good but REALLY strong. The first few sips were great, but once the flavor settled a little bit the last few were hard to get through.

name: Home Coffee Roasters
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Very well lit, great wifi, great people, great spot to hang out and chat or get a lot of work done. I sat there for quite a few hours, first working and then people watching and never got tired of it. 

Taste: 5 / 5. The coffee was awesome! The espresso flavor was on the sweeter side but the coffee had a great balance. Would get again.
visit_again: 4 - Would come again if I’m anywhere in the city
vibe_thoughts: Very well lit, great wifi, great people, great spot to hang out and chat or get a lot of work done. I sat there for quite a few hours, first working and then people watching and never got tired of it.
taste_thoughts: The coffee was awesome! The espresso flavor was on the sweeter side but the coffee had a great balance. Would get again.

name: Telve Cafe
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. There’s a super cozy corner which I unfortunately didn’t get to sit in but I knew I’d spent a long time in if I did. Great wifi, great working atmosphere, good vibes. They had a sand heating setup for Turkish coffee which was quite cool too.

Taste: 4 / 5. My first taste of Turkish Coffee! It was pitched to me as “bold as espresso but not as bitter” and honestly held completely true to the description. I still prefer espresso, but definitely worth the experience.
visit_again: 3 - Would visit again if I’m in the area
vibe_thoughts: There’s a super cozy corner which I unfortunately didn’t get to sit in but I knew I’d spent a long time in if I did. Great wifi, great working atmosphere, good vibes. They had a sand heating setup for Turkish coffee which was quite cool too.
taste_thoughts: My first taste of Turkish Coffee! It was pitched to me as “bold as espresso but not as bitter” and honestly held completely true to the description. I still prefer espresso, but definitely worth the experience.

name: Blackbird Bookstore and Cafe
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. It’s a bookstore, of course it has great vibes. This place has a very nice backyard (with a deconstructable golden gate bridge) and super cute seating which is private enough despite being in a shared space. Very cool design. 

Taste: 3 / 5. Their cortado was VERY bold. And by that I mean the espresso taste was a little overpowering. A great tasting espresso, but overpowering nonetheless.

name: HITW Coffee
thoughts:
Vibe: 5 / 5. Honestly, this was a fascinating place, definitely one if its kind of all the places I’ve been to so far. The barista there was incredible, she chatted with us for a while while our coffee was being made (apparently it’s just 1 person that runs the shop, the owner aside). She told us the lore of how their specialty, the coco cold brew came to be - one of their hungover neighbors would come to the shop, get a coconut water and then cold brew before their way out. One day, they were running late, so they mixed the two and voila, the unique drink was formed. The environment was very comfortable, reminded me of a regular tea stall you might go to on your way out of the house in India. 

Taste: 5 / 5. My friend ordered the coco cold brew and that was fascinating. Had 3 layers of taste, and it was honestly unlike anything I’d had before. Their espresso machine wasn’t working and I got the North Beach, and despite not being the biggest non-espresso coffee drinker, this was fantastic. The notes came through in the pour over, it was sweet but just the right amount.
visit_again: 6 - Would fly in to come to this place again

thoughts:

Taste: 5 / 5. One of the best espresso based drinks I’ve ever had. I got the Warhol2.0, which was coconut + citrus + cinnamon and espresso and it was incredible. Every sip was amazing, and the flavors balanced out each other very very well.
